Review: This movie is sort of like if James Cameron facehugged Ridley Scott and implanted Ridley with a movie that burst out of his chest
The Dutch in old Amsterdam do it,Not to mention the Finns!
Dear Kermit, Wocka Wocka Wocka. But seriously,
If ghosts can sext,What is next?
At the beginning of this movie Stevie Wonder was singing “When you believe in Things that you don’t understand,” and I was like, “Aw geez — you don’t know the HALF of it, Stevie!”
From the director of the music video for Virtual Insanity
Epilogue: and then between this film and the original all of Willy’s friends died and he became a resentful, solitary hermit
“I been thinkin’ what to do with my future. I could be a mud doctor. Checkin’ out the earth. Underneath.”
A maniacal barrage of incident and spectacle, defiantly unconcerned with the why in favor of the what. It is a tale told by a genius, full of sound and Ridley, signifying nothing.
